sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User
    participant Server as Server (PHP)
    participant DB as Database
    participant Admin as Admin Browser
    participant Local as Admin Local Machine

    %% Configuration Phase
    Note over Admin,Server: Configuration Phase
    Local->>Local: Generate RSA Key Pair (Public & Private)
    Local->>Server: Upload public_key.pem
    Note over Server: Server stores public_key.pem

    %% Upload Phase
    Note over User,DB: Customer KYC Submission
    User->>Server: Submit KYC Data & Passport Image
    
    %% Failsafe Check
    alt public_key.pem is missing
        Server-->>User: Graceful Error: "System Maintenance"
    else public_key.pem exists
        %% Hybrid Encryption
        Note over Server: Hybrid Encryption Process
        Server->>Server: 1. Encrypt Text (Name, DOB) with RSA Public Key
        Server->>Server: 2. Generate Random 256-bit AES Key & IV
        Server->>Server: 3. Encrypt Passport Image with AES Key
        Server->>Server: 4. Encrypt AES Key with RSA Public Key
        Server->>Server: 5. Delete Plaintext Image from Disk
        
        %% Storage
        Server->>DB: Store RSA-Encrypted Text
        Server->>DB: Store RSA-Encrypted AES Key + IV
        Server->>Server: Store AES-Encrypted Image File
        Server-->>User: "Pending Admin Review"
    end

    %% Review Phase
    Note over Admin,DB: Admin Review Phase (Zero-Knowledge)
    Admin->>Server: Request Pending KYC Records
    Server->>DB: Fetch Encrypted Records
    DB-->>Server: Encrypted Records
    Server-->>Admin: Return Encrypted Base64 Data & Encrypted Image Paths
    
    Note over Admin: UI shows [Encrypted Data] masks
    
    Admin->>Local: Select private_key.pem (File Picker)
    Note over Admin: Client-Side Decryption (Javascript)
    Local-->>Admin: Read private_key.pem locally
    Admin->>Admin: 1. Decrypt Text with RSA Private Key
    Admin->>Admin: 2. Decrypt AES Key with RSA Private Key
    Admin->>Admin: 3. Fetch Encrypted Image Blob
    Admin->>Admin: 4. Decrypt Image Blob using AES Key
    Admin->>Admin: 5. Render Blob URL in Browser
    Note over Admin: Admin views plaintext data. Private key never leaves browser.
